    <h3 id="img-caption">A true loving couple!</h3>

    <article>
	<h4>Fairytales vs Real life</h4>
	<p>Every girl dreams of relationships and marriage in terms of all the fairytales she has seen. Sleeping Beauty, Snow White, Princess Bride, etc. They all have the same thing in common. Some poor miserable girl is saved by a handsome prince, who shows up as a knight and whisks her off to a magical land.</p>
        <p>It rarely happens. Typically a girl feels like she's an old maid if she doesn't have a boyfriend in school. She allows herself to sink into self doubt if she doesn't marry some jock by the age of 23. To this end nearly every girl does whatever it takes, literally, to catch the good-looking jock who looks good on her arm; the envy of all the other girls.</p>
        <p>Long about the first kid or two she sees a change. The handsome jock is spending less and less time at home, and when he does he's not so nice. By the second or third kid she's done with all of that and is in queue for a divorce.</p>
	<p>Oh, if only she knew what awaited her through her sorrow!</p>
        <p>Along with her divorce comes an old familiar song. "Some day my prince will come." "Why can't I find my own knight in shining armour."</p>
    </article>
