	<h4>Wishes can come true</h4>
	<p>So she goes to the witches in the forest, or in this case mother and friends, and asks for a potion. She is oblighed in the form of a fun-filled day at the ren-fare. Surely there has to be a knight in shining armour there, ey? Well, as Jiminy Cricket sang...</p>
        <p style="text-align:center">A Dream Is A Wish Your Heart Makes</p>
        <p style="text-align:center">A dream is a wish your heart makes</p>
        <p style="text-align:center">When you're fast asleep</p>
        <p style="text-align:center">In dreams you lose your heartaches</p>
        <p style="text-align:center">Whatever you wish for, you keep</p>
        <br>
        <p style="text-align:center">Have faith in your dreams and someday</p>
        <p style="text-align:center">Your rainbow will come smiling through</p>
        <p style="text-align:center">No matter how your heart is grieving</p>
        <p style="text-align:center">If you keep on believing</p>
        <p style="text-align:center">the dream that you wish will come true</p>
        <br>
        <p>And...wah lah! A knight in shining armour REALLY DID show up! Honest! Okay, so the meeting wasn't exactly perfect. It's true, a knight in armour did come up to her; but he was drug over by a scholarly friend. That's okay, but when it's ninty-two degrees out and you're in a tin can, its hard to knightly.</p>
        <p>And so it was that the princess could only feel sorry for the poor knight and the knight was cooking in that tin can so he couldn't really find her as beautiful as perhaps he should have. If Jimminy was right, they would get another chance.</p>
    </article>
