    <article>
	<h4>If it's meant to be</h4>
	<p>If it's written in the stars, they say, you will meet again. Well I don't know about the stars, but this one princess did meet that knight again. She didn't know it was him. Oh no! It was six months later and her knight was running around in a kilt at the highland games.</p>
	<p style="text-align:center">"Nice!", says she, "but it wouldn't be proper to just strike up a conversation.</p>
	<p style="text-align:center">"Nice!", says he, "but it wouldn't be proper to talk to her without being properly introduced.</p>
	<p style="text-align:center">"Posh!", says the same two witches.</p>
	<p style="text-align:center">"Nonscence!",says the same old scholar. "This is America. I will ask them all out."</p>
	<p>And so the old scholar did just that. He drug over the kilted Welshman over to the princess and witches and introduced himself and his friend.</p>
	<p>Perhaps it was the fact that older people can tell when people are in love. Or perhaps it was just that older people have moved past the pain and say "what the heck". Whatever the case, the nudging and support brought these two together."
	<p>For this couple it was truly magic! 
