  <div id="tribute-info">
    <p>I have known many many couples and have lived many many years. The story of love is as old as time. Books and fairytales have been written upon the subject, but only once upon a time does the love last. A true love comes but once in a lifetime and often gets missed. This one couple adore each other, but oddly they missed it. Everyone around them kept holding their breath waiting for them to realize how much in love they were. Too proper, too shy, too scared to reach out. But for the fairytale witch and a scholar, they would have been ships that passed in the night. Sometimes, however, fairytales do come true - if you wish just right upon that star. Alasdair and Courtney, an old Welsh bachelor and a disillusioned Scotswoman found each other against the odds and LIVED HAPPILY EVER AFTER for real!<p>
